  langs: []
  S_playerDiags:
  - commentCount: 1
    s_comment:
    - text: Yes, Detective? Me and Defendant 1 are innocent. We were just studying
        our vocabulary lists together.
      extraData: ExtraData
      inputSetIndex: 0
      outputNodeIndex: 1
      outActionIndex: -1
      sprites: {fileID: 0}
      audios: {fileID: 0}
      visible: 1
    ID: 0
    pTag: Defendant 2
    sprite: {fileID: 0}
    vars: []
    varKeys: []
    isPlayer: 0
  - commentCount: 3
    s_comment:
    - text: You used a double negative in that sentence; a person who breaks grammar
        rules surely breaks school rules!
      extraData: ExtraData
      inputSetIndex: 1
      outputNodeIndex: -1
      outActionIndex: -1
      sprites: {fileID: 0}
      audios: {fileID: 0}
      visible: 1
    - text: You used 'Me' as a subject pronoun instead of 'I'; that grammatical slip-up
        reveals your hidden guilt!
      extraData: ExtraData
      inputSetIndex: 1
      outputNodeIndex: 2
      outActionIndex: -1
      sprites: {fileID: 0}
      audios: {fileID: 0}
      visible: 1
    - text: Your subject and verb do not agree in that statement; I suspect your
        story is just as mismatched as your tense!
      extraData: ExtraData
      inputSetIndex: 1
      outputNodeIndex: -1
      outActionIndex: -1
      sprites: {fileID: 0}
      audios: {fileID: 0}
      visible: 1
    ID: 1
    pTag: Detective
    sprite: {fileID: 0}
    vars: []
    varKeys: []
    isPlayer: 1
  - commentCount: 1
    s_comment:
    - text: Ugh, my English teacher would be so disappointed! Okay, I was near the
        desk. But I saw Defendant 3 hiding something in their backpack very suspiciously!
      extraData: ExtraData
      inputSetIndex: 2
      outputNodeIndex: -1
      outActionIndex: -1
      sprites: {fileID: 0}
      audios: {fileID: 0}
      visible: 1
    ID: 2
    pTag: Defendant 2
    sprite: {fileID: 0}
